titulo: Jeans Motherhood Maternity
comentario: I really like these jeans but the sizing is off. I bought both the small and medium to compare and see which which sizing felt best to me. I'm a size 4 prepregnancy and according to the chart should be a small but am generally between sizes so ordered both just in case, and I'm glad I did. The jeans are stretchy and I like the medium wash but the small pair I received is bigger than the medium pair. (See photos) The colors are slightly different too with the medium being a bit lighter than the small but not a big difference. I tried on the medium first and was surprised to see they felt a bit tight (still wearable but tighter than I would have thought/preferred). I wasn't even going to bother trying on the small but realized the small looked bigger than the medium so tried on and they felt similar but a bit loser than the medium. I then measured them because I thought that was odd and sure enough the small is bigger. I double checked the tags inside and the sizing is correct and the styles are identical so not sure what happened. Length fits me great - I'm 5'2'' and debated ordering petite but glad I ordered the regular instead. I wanted to purchase another pair in a different color as well but can't due to not knowing wht size to order!

titulo: Olympus Câmera À Prova D'Água Olympus Tough Tg-6, Preto
comentario: I have used Olympus cameras for many years now. I am a stock photographer and sell a large number of photos each month. I have been selling my underwater photos since the 1970s and I was excited about having a small camera I could use underwater. I was very pleased with the camera. Small, tough body and great features. You can imagine my surprise when I saw terrible Chromatic aberration in my landscape photos. Terrible noise photos and were only sharp in macro mode. I thought it must be a defect. I sent the camera back to Olympus to have it checked out. Got it back. No change. My iPhone 13pro takes much better, and more usable photos than this camera. I hope Olympus places a new lens and chip in the TG7. I would pay double for a camera like this I could use.

titulo: Camera Digital Panasonic Lumix DC-FZ80
comentario: I really like this camera - it seems a great value for the money.  (I got it at a sale price, too:  $297.  That price comes around every so often, and is worth waiting for IMO.)It's not top of the line, but it's light and very easy to use.  The zoom is fantastic.  I use to it photograph birds, mostly, and other animals as well - and you can get good images from very far away without scaring them away.  Again, not top of the line, but really quite good for the price.  The telephoto lens can go bad, I've read, as mine did - after three years it  sometimes stopped extending and I have to shut the camera off and on again to make it work.  After 4 years and some rough handling by me, it still does work well for far-away subjects, although at this point the wide-angle view is fuzzy around the edges; I bought another one which I'll take better care of, and still use the old one to bang around with.  I also own a pretty good camera with a good telephoto lens - but this is my day-to-day go-to camera for hiking.  I'm not a pro; just in it for the enjoyment.

titulo: Canon Câmera digital PowerShot SX540 com zoom óptico de 50x – Wi-Fi e NFC habilitado (preto), 1-1067C001
comentario: For what it is - an inexpensive bridge camera - this product holds up. It produces image of a quality comparable to DSLRs and with a wide range of user-friendly settings that make lining up and making a photograph straightforward and simple. However, there are drawbacks to any bridge camera, and they certainly don't offer the range of photographic freedoms that DSLRs do, even if the images they produce can be evenly compared in terms of technical quality. Someone looking for a good camera for vernacular photography, family vacations, and things of this nature will not be disappointed by the flexibility of this camera, nor the image quality, and at a price not much higher than one might expect of the point-and-shoot more common of the genre, it's a steal. but serious photographers, even relatively poor ones like myself, would benefit tremendously by the freedom and flexibility offered for the hundred extra dollars it would take to buy a DSLR of comparable quality.Go9od at what it's good at, bad at what it's not. Reasonably-priced either way.

titulo: Câmera Digital Lumix DMC-ZS80 Panasonic Preta
comentario: I was looking for a camera for an upcoming trip to South America. Although my iPhone 13 Pro takes great photos, it has limited telephoto capabilities, so I decided to buy a "real" camera instead, one that was both compact in size but had good optical zoom.After considering both the Panasonic Lumix ZS80 and very similar Nikon Coolpix A1000, I decided to order the Lumix. After playing with it for a couple of days, I decided to return it, primarily for two reasons:1. The fonts on the screen and camera controls are very small, and hard for me to read without reading glasses, which I don't plan to wear outside. That might have become less of an issue after I became more familiar with the camera, but I didn't want to have to struggle with it on my upcoming trip. Note that reading the fonts was not a problem when using the viewfinder rather than the touchscreen.2. The feature that allows you to automatically transfer photos from the camera to your phone using the Panasonic app was pretty quirky. Even though the camera can connect to the phone via Bluetooth, you have to connect the phone to the camera's WiFi in order to transfer photos.A couple of other observations: there are two manuals, basic and advanced. A printed copy of the basic manual is included, but you have to access the advanced online. Also, the cover over the charging and HDMI ports is very flimsy and seems like it might fall off.I can't evaluate the camera's performance since I didn't use it enough. It appears well built (other than the port cover) and feels comfortable in your hand. It's pretty small, so it should be easy to pack. I also ordered a case, extra battery, battery charger, and memory cards (none come with the camera), but returned everything except the memory card that I opened.Sorry it didn't work out for me, but if your eyes are better than mine, the camera is worth considering.

titulo: Câmera digital Sony Cyber-shot DSC-H300
comentario: Update June 20, 2019:My second set of NiMH batteries just went flat after taking photo number 1488. So I am getting on average 744 photos per charge on a set of rechargeable NiMH batteries. That is really good battery performance.The Sony DSC-H300 is a very nice camera for the price. It is not equal to a Rebel SLR or my Fuji, but it costs a fraction of the price of either of those.  For a basic point and shoot camera it has a lot going for it.The user interface is about the same as most digital cameras, so you should be able to figure it out. I had very little trouble with it.The complete operator manual is available by going to sony dot com and digging down through support.The photographs are sharp enough. The colors are a bit more saturated than they are in my other cameras, but that is what I have noticed in Sony cameras that I have owned previously.The autofocus can be a bit tricky, but with practice I am mostly able to make it work. I take a lot of macro photos, and sometimes it does better using the area focus, and sometimes it does better using the spot focus. I try things until it works.I was initially put off by the fact that there is no obvious Macro setting.  I take a lot of macro photographs.  However, the camera does have a macro mode; it sets it automatically, removing the need to remember to put it into macro mode before shooting. So the lack of a menu setting for macros is a benifit rather than a deficiency.I also was initially put off by having to set the exposure correction through the menu system. You have to push the menu button, then click down a few spaces to get to the EV setting. It takes four or five menu clicks.  However, once I had set the EV to something other than zero, pushing the Menu button took me directy to the EV menu, so it became a one-click setting at that point. Clever. In fact the menu does that in general. The menu rembembers where it was and takes you back there when you push the Menu button. That memory is reset when you go in and out of replay mode or turn the camera on/off.The camera uses AA batteries, which is a requirement for me. I have boxes of NiMH rechargeables that I use in all of my cameras, and the DSC-H300 works fine with them.  I shot 646 photographs on one set of fully charged Eneloop 1900 mAh NiMH batteries.  That is not an estimate; I actually took that many photos on one set of batteries. It reports the charge level accurately as well.For connection to a computer, the camera uses a Mini USB 5-pin connector, not to be confused with the older USB mini 4-pin connector, which is larger. I have some older cameras that use a connector that is called a "Mini USB", but it is not the same connector as the one that works with this Sony.  The older connector is more accurately referred to as a "Mini USB 4-pin" connector.  Fortunately, the camera came with the proper cable, so this was not an immediate issue, but if you need to replace the cable, make sure that you get the "Mini USB 5-pin" version.A nice feature is that the backup battery that maintains the settings, such as the clock when the main batteries are out is rechargeable. So if you leave the camera with no batteries in it long enough for the backup battery to go flat, you can simply leave fresh AA batteries in it for a while and the backup battery will recharge.  You don't have to buy a replacement cell to put into the camera.One of my favorite features of this camera is that it allows me to decide whether to connect to a computer using Picture Transfer Protocol (PTP) or USB Mass Storage. PTP is a camera-specific protocal that connects to the computer in a readonly fashion. That makes it very unlikely that I can do something stupid and damage the SD card. In PTP mode, unmounting the card just requires turning off the camera.  If you want to change anything on the card using the computer you have the option to connect to the computer as Mass Storage USB. That protocol gives you full access to the SD card. Just be careful to unmount the card before pulling the plug or turning off the camera or you risk damaging the file system on the card and losing your images. I use PTP because it is simpler and safer.The camera connects properly to USB on Windows 7, Linux Mint 18.1 and Linux Mageia 7 Beta 1. It connects using both USB 2.0 and USB 3.0 ports.Caveat: It is necessary to take off the lens cover before turning on the camera.  When you turn on the camera, the lens moves out slightly, and the lens cap blocks that motion. If you leave the lens cap on, the camera throws an error telling you to turn off the camera and try again. So always take the lens cover off before turning on the camera. An exception to this rule is that you can leave the lens cover on when it is connected to a computer. It does not attempt to move the lens when it is connected to the USB.Here is another tip.  The instruction manual says that to change a menu setting, find and set the new setting, then push the OK button to select it. However, pushing the OK button makes the menu disappear. If you are setting multiple items in the menu, it is annoying to go back into the menu for each item.  However, you can set multiple items easily. To set multiple items, select the desired item and setting, then push the Down button or the Up button to accept the new setting. The menu will remain displayed, and the new setting will be accepted.So I give high marks to the Sony DSC-H300 as a beginner camera or a less expensive knock-around shop camera. If you are looking to take truly outstanding photographs to print in large format, you might want to look around and spend more. But for a general purpose camera, the DSC-H300 works.

The advanced software available from Dymo's site is even better.* OK looking design, but a little oversized* You can get noname replacement tapes to save money(although I haven't tried them)* I believe there is a limited selection of tape widths too - which offers you some flexibilityNot So Great* Small fonts don't look too great (i.e. if you make a four line label)* Not high resolution, but satisfactory for most needs* At full price, not the best value. comentario: I have waited to write a review because I wanted to use it for a few months first. I received this for Christmas, but I also picked this one out for my husband to get me. I read all the reviews about the leaking, noise, the length of time it takes and the frother. I also read all the great reviews. I decided out of all the machines out there, this one seemed to be the one that would most likely work in our kitchen and for our lattes.After using this machine for 3 months I can confirm it is noisy, but so are the ones at the coffee houses and it really does not bother me at all. If you are an earlier riser and you family will be annoyed with you for making your espresso or latte in the morning this may not be the right one for you. Does it leak. NO it does not leak. These people who say it leaks must be the laziest people on the planet. It will only leak if you do not remove water from the bottom where your cup sits. I also always dump the water after I am done making my coffee. It takes a while to warm up. If the light turns to a steady light before 5 mins it is not ready. For sure give it 5-10 mins to heat up. The frother works great if you heat up your cold milk first in the microwave just for a min. Otherwise it does take a little while. The foam is perfect. I bought a coffee grinder from XO and grinds the beans to the perfect espresso powder. The coffee tastes great. The coffee maker works great too. If you want a faster machine you will need to spend a $1000-$2000 for sure. I was not willing to do that since I still like to go to my local Starbucks.I am completely satisfied with this machine. My kids love it too.

comentario: Still a great bag, but I feel like my old traditional style back pack had a lot more room in it. This one has tons of different pockets, but you can't actually fit very much into them. All the pockets are extremely tight. I struggled to wedge my laptop into this bag and one of the corners still sticks out. It fits decently in the main compartment but not in the laptop section.The mesh bottle pockets are also extremely small. I think this bag was more designed to fit under a seat and everything you put on it just gets crushed to fit the dimensions. I had to get extremely creative to fit the few items I have in it.The shoe compartment is useless as it takes up the already limited space inside the main compartment. The pocket on the back is also very tight and shallow. I could fit either my phone or my wallet, but not both.I feel like I was a little misled by the tiktok reviews that got me to purchase this. I was made to believe you could fit a laptop and a couple days worth of clothes plus shoes and toiletries plus a phone and wallet and keys or meds..... this bag barely fits my laptop, switch, one RX bottle, a box of ibuprofen and my headphones.Good things about the bag :I like the strap on the back to hold your bag to a roller suitcase. Definitely helped save my back.The power bank port is nice. I have a larger power bank and that did not help my case with the lack of space, but being able to plug into the exterior of my bag instead of digging around for the bank at the bottom of my bag to use it was nice.The wet pocket is cool. comentario: I recently bought the VEWIOR H13 True HEPA Air Purifier for my large, 600-square-foot bedroom, and I have to say that it has exceeded my expectations. This air cleaner has made a huge difference in how clean the air is in my home.One of the most impressive things about the VEWIOR H13 is how well it cleans the air. It has a real HEPA filter that works well to catch and get rid of 99.97% of airborne particles as small as 0.3 microns. This means it easily gets rid of dust, pet dander, pollen, and even dangerous volatile organic compounds (VOCs). Since I've been using this air purifier, I've noticed a big drop in allergens and smells.This air purifier is different from others because it can clean the air in larger rooms. It's easy to clean and move the air in my bedroom, which is up to 600 square feet big. The unit has a strong motor that doesn't make a lot of noise, so it can run all day and night without waking anyone up. I like that I can breathe in clean, fresh air without being bothered by noise.The VEWIOR H13 also has smart air quality sensors that can find out how clean the air is in real time. The display panel shows me how clean the air is right now, so I can keep an eye on it and change the settings as needed. The automatic mode is especially convenient because the purifier adjusts the speed of the fan based on the air quality it detects, so it always works at its best.This air purifier is easy to take care of. Changing the filter is simple and doesn't cause any trouble. I like how the filter replacement indicator lets me know when it's time to change the filter, which keeps the purifier running at its best.Another good thing about the VEWIOR H13 is that it looks sleek and modern. titulo: Social: Why Our Brains Are Wired to Connect (English Edition)
comentario: The book basically reviews recent brain science experiments, and how these relate to the society in which we live.  Don't let the science scare you, it is explained well.  The author makes an effort to explain the significance of the science experiments and only goes to the detail required to understand how it relates to the discussion at hand.The material will make you think and reflect.  The material has some counter intuitive punches that will reverse some of your previously conceived ideas about society.If you were to use current Canadian and US politics as representative of the state of society you might be a little cynical about societies future.  However within these pages there is some basic hope of how we are wired as humans that gives me hope, that we will overcome some of these issues in the future.One of the challenges is that the people who need to read the book won't, which is too bad, because if the science in the book is right, well that is why you need to read the book.If you care about society and where it is going, this will give you hope through scientific understanding.  If you only care about yourself, and how you can take advantage of society, you might want to read it, as you will probably discover your own worst enemy is yourself.  Ah, well poetic justice always makes for a good story.I will be reflecting on this material for sometime.  It will likely have to be read again, as while reading it the material sparked so many side trips in my wandering mind, that I had to often back track to reestablish contact with the author.  Again making it a worthwhile read.Be well, and treat each other excellently.  (Now there is scientific proof of this.)
